{"lemma":"عُزْبُ","slug":"عُزْبُ","root":"ع.ز.ب","root_slug":"ع-ز-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ز-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28937","n28941"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B2%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28937","headword_ar":"عَزَبَ","root":"Ezb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzuwbN","text_ar":"عُزُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absent;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~iY","text_ar":"عَنِّى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEzb","text_ar":"اعزب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the former meaning: (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazaba","text_ar":"عَزَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n. as above, (K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, absent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazaba bihaA","text_ar":"عَزَبَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", referring to sheep or goats,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far off, with them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in a trad.: or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bhA","text_ar":"بها"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ez~b","text_ar":"عزّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went with them to a remote pasturage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pastured them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, camels,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at a distance from the place of abode of the tribe, not repairing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning, to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the evening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~b","text_ar":"تعزّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus the verb is written in copies of the K in a place where some copies have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEozubu","text_ar":"يَعْزُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurs in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~b Eano A^aholihi wamaAlihi","text_ar":"تعزّب عَنْ اَهْلِهِ وَمَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away to a distance from his family and his cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazabati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"عَزَبَتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels went away to a distance in the pasturage, not returning in the evening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) and in like manner one says of sheep or goats. (O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA","text_ar":"لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEozubu Eano Eilomihi $aYo'N","text_ar":"يَعْزُبُ عَنْ عِلْمِهِ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing is absent from his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See Kur x.62 and xxxiv. 3.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazaba Tuhoru AlmuroA^api","text_ar":"عَزَبَ طُهْرُ المُرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman's state of pureness from the menstrual discharge was a remote thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the woman's husband was absent from her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or [rather] is said of the woman when her husband is absent from her. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazaba Eano fulaAnK Hilomuhu","text_ar":"عَزَبَ عَنْ فُلَانٍ حِلْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one's forbearance quitted him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEzb","text_ar":"اعزب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzobapN","text_ar":"عُزْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzuwbapN","text_ar":"عُزُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, MF, TA,) or these are simple substs., (S, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was without a wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of celibacy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) [And app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazabato","text_ar":"عَزَبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said in like manner of a woman, meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was without a husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also 5.] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazabati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"عَزَبَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether fruitful or unfruitful,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, destitute of inhabitants; had in it no one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","MF","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n28941","headword_ar":"عَزَبٌ","root":"Ezb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[correctly thus, but in the sense here following written in the TA without any syll. signs, and in the O written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~abN","text_ar":"عِزَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who goes away to a distance into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) [And One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who goes far away with his camels to pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziybN","text_ar":"عَزِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEozibN","text_ar":"مُعْزِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaAbapN","text_ar":"مِعْزَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiraAwapu","text_ar":"هِرَاوَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEozaAbi","text_ar":"الاَعْزَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The staff of those who go far away with their camels to pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a horse is likened thereto, (S, O, TA,) on account of its compactness and smoothness; so in a marginal note in the L: (TA:) [Sgh, however, says,] thus in some of the lexicons, but in my opinion, (O,) it was the name of a mare which was not to be outstripped, and which was thus called because her owner gave her gratuitously for the use of those of his people who had no wives, who made predatory attacks upon her, and when one of them acquired for himself property and a wife, he resigned her to another of his people: (O, K: *) whence the prov."},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aEaz~u mino hiraAwapi AlA^aEozaAbi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More highly esteemed than Hiráwet-el-Aazáb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadiydN","text_ar":"عَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also Whatever is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alone, solitary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, * TA,) which is the original; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziybN","text_ar":"عَزِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaAbapN","text_ar":"مِعْزَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see below]; (K;) but not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozaAbu","text_ar":"اَعْزَابُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, O, Msb, K,) this being disallowed by AHát, (O, Msb,) and others; (TA;) or it is rare; (K;) but it occurs in a trad.; (Mgh, O;) and some allow it: (O, Msb:) the pl. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euz~aAbN","text_ar":"عُزَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Msb,) which is thus because the original form of the sing. is considered as being ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", this pl. being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuf~aArN","text_ar":"كُفَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfirN","text_ar":"كَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabN","text_ar":"عَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has both of these pls., (O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euz~aAbN","text_ar":"عُزَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and is applied to men and to (assumed tropical:)  women as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no spouses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabapN","text_ar":"عَزَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to (assumed tropical:)  a woman [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no husband"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Ks, S, O, Msb, K,) and (O, Msb, K) so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabN","text_ar":"عَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Zj, Kz, Mgh,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2034},{"kind":"text","text":"O, Msb, K;) and if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozabu","text_ar":"اَعْزَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"be applied to a man, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazobaA='u","text_ar":"عَزْبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", may by rule be applied to a woman; and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabapN","text_ar":"عَزَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabaAtN","text_ar":"عَزَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or, accord. to Zj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabapN","text_ar":"عَزَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake of Abu-l-'Abbás [i. e. Th], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabN","text_ar":"عَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as an epithet of a man and of a woman, like as is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSomN","text_ar":"خَصْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and does not assume a dual form nor a pl. nor a fem. form, because it is originally an inf. n.; MF, however, denies that we have any authority for calling"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabN","text_ar":"عَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n.: he considers it to be a simple epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and if used in the fem. sense without the termination"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"otherwise than by poetic license, to be an anomalous epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAnisN","text_ar":"عَانِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied alike to a man and to a woman: the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulaAni EazabaAni","text_ar":"رَجُلَانِ عَزَبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also mentioned: and the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laEazabN lazabN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَعَزَبٌ لَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which the latter epithet is merely an imitative sequent corrobative of the former], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA laEazabapN lazabapN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لَعَزَبَةٌ لَزَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazabN","text_ar":"عَزَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be [also] a quasi-pl. n. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAzibN","text_ar":"عَازِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdimN","text_ar":"خَادِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","Mgh","Msb","K","Ks"]}]}}